<p>A more general problem is to count <a href="/wiki/Spanning_tree" title="Spanning tree">spanning trees</a> in an <a href="/wiki/Undirected_graph" class="mw-redirect" title="Undirected graph">undirected graph</a>, which is addressed by the <a href="/wiki/Matrix_tree_theorem" class="mw-redirect" title="Matrix tree theorem">matrix tree theorem</a>. (Cayley's formula is the special case of spanning trees in a <a href="/wiki/Complete_graph" title="Complete graph">complete graph</a>.) The similar problem of counting all the subtrees regardless of size is <a href="/wiki/Sharp-P-complete" class="mw-redirect" title="Sharp-P-complete">#P-complete</a> in the general case (<a href="#CITEREFJerrum1994">Jerrum (1994)</a>).
</p>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id="Unlabeled_trees">Unlabeled trees</h3><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Tree_(graph_theory)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11" title="Edit section: Unlabeled trees"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
